headline: Disney+ Churn Rate: The One Number That Shows If Streaming Is Working
summary: Disney doesn’t report Disney+ churn rates. That silence tells you everything. While Netflix (NASDAQ:NFLX) doesn’t publicly disclose specific monthly churn figures, Walt Disney (NYSE:DIS) won’t disclose the number at all. Here’s why it matters: churn reveals whether you’re building a library people keep paying for or a content treadmill they hop on and off. The ... headline: The Melania Movie Looks Like a Box-Office Flop. What It Means for Amazon.
summary: When it comes to the streaming wars, investors have tended to see  Amazon.com  as an afterthought.  The company’s new documentary about Melania Trump looks unlikely to change that.  At first glance, that’s a solid-enough opening weekend for a documentary—but it pales in comparison to what Amazon has spent on “Melania.”
